the victim as Meredith Roberts.

11
00:01:50,052 --> 00:01:53,294
No obvious signs of violence.
Are we saying it wasn't the Weevil?

12
00:01:53,288 --> 00:01:57,975
Give me a chance, Miss Cooper.
I've only just started.
'Jack, your VIP visitor is here.'

13
00:01:57,966 --> 00:02:00,287
I didn't realise
we were having a visitor.

14
00:02:00,282 --> 00:02:05,322
Suddenly, in an underground
mortuary, on a wet night in Cardiff,
I hear the song of a nightingale.

15
00:02:09,274 --> 00:02:11,640
Miss Martha Jones.

16
00:02:25,773 --> 00:02:27,695
Oh, it's good to see you, Jack.

17
00:02:29,571 --> 00:02:33,291
Toshiko, Owen, Gwen,

18
00:02:33,288 --> 00:02:36,166
Ianto, meet Martha.

19
00:02:36,164 --> 00:02:38,166
Just a casual visit or. . . ?

20
00:02:38,161 --> 00:02:40,561
I'm here to complete your postmortem.

21
00:02:40,559 --> 00:02:42,686
Dr Jones is from UNIT.

22
00:02:42,678 --> 00:02:46,921
Oh, I'm sorry, sorry, I get
a bit confused. Which one's UNIT?

23
00:02:46,912 --> 00:02:49,403
Intelligence, military,
cute red caps.

24
00:02:49,393 --> 00:02:53,079
The acceptable face of
intelligence gathering on aliens.

25
00:02:53,070 --> 00:02:56,426
We're more ad hoc.
But better looking.

26
00:02:56,423 --> 00:03:00,143
I identified a pattern
from UNIT's data on sudden deaths.

27
00:03:00,141 --> 00:03:05,659
Toxic shock. Nothing to link
the victims. Different ages, sexes,
ethnic origins, occupations.

28
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:09,656
But there was
a statistically significant
concentration in South Wales.

29
00:03:09,649 --> 00:03:13,403
Come on, Martha, be honest. You
just came all this way to see me.

30
00:03:13,403 --> 00:03:16,531
Still struggling to conquer
your shyness, Jack?

31
00:03:16,523 --> 00:03:20,596
So what about this pattern,
then, Dr Jones?

32
00:03:20,596 --> 00:03:24,202
They were being written off
as suicides or accidents.

33
00:03:24,195 --> 00:03:26,277
Look.

34
00:03:27,311 --> 00:03:29,916
Puncture mark.

35
00:03:29,907 --> 00:03:34,867
Hypodermic needle.
You'll find his bloodstream was
pumped full of ammonium hydroxide.

36
00:03:34,866 --> 00:03:36,788
Bloodstream.
I was going to do that next.

37
00:03:36,782 --> 00:03:39,501
Have you checked his medical records?
No. I wasjust about to.

38
00:03:39,499 --> 00:03:43,697
Let's give it a go. You never know,
Owen, you might learn something.

39
00:03:46,131 --> 00:03:49,851
One Meredith Roberts, age 45.

40
00:03:49,845 --> 00:03:53,326
I know there's been a major crash
on the NHS system.

41
00:03:53,321 --> 00:03:55,528
Wiped a shedload of files.

42
00:03:55,519 --> 00:04:00,081
Including all the victims I flagged
up from the UNIT data. And now yours.

43
00:04:00,075 --> 00:04:03,636
A computer crash wouldn't delete
data so cleanly. This is deliberate.

44
00:04:03,632 --> 00:04:05,190
Let me look into it.

45
00:04:05,189 --> 00:04:07,987
How's the family? Getting better.

46
00:04:07,987 --> 00:04:10,387
They send their love. Give them mine.

47
00:04:10,387 --> 00:04:15,108
So, End of the World Survivors Club.

48
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:17,216
God, I am so glad to see you, Jack!

49
00:04:17,215 --> 00:04:20,503
See, you did come all this way
just to see me. It's the jaw line.

50
00:04:20,492 --> 00:04:22,175
Once seen, always yearned for.

51
00:04:27,607 --> 00:04:29,245
D'you miss him?

52
00:04:29,243 --> 00:04:33,088
No. I made my choice.

53
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:37,198
Maybe sometimes. Ah!
Tiny bit. Tiny, tiny.

54
00:04:37,197 --> 00:04:40,598
Then I come to my senses again.
Anyway, I've got plenty to occupy me.

55
00:04:40,594 --> 00:04:43,961
Oh, yeah, Miss Highfalutin'.
What is it? Medical officer?

56
