about this.

84
00:06:19,564 --> 00:06:22,852
But for my money, it's got to be
a surgical instrument. Really?

85
00:06:22,845 --> 00:06:24,847
He's guessing. Typical medic. Hmm.

86
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:27,049
Well,
I call it a singularity scalpel.

87
00:06:27,038 --> 00:06:33,398
See, what it does is concentrates
energy on a tiny fixed point without
damaging anything on the way.

88
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:38,547
It's brilliant. It's amazing. Yeah,
do you remember the last time
you did that, Owen. . . ? Yes.

89
00:06:38,547 --> 00:06:42,665
Right, now,
all we're going to do is,
we're going to vaporise this paper

90
00:06:42,664 --> 00:06:45,986
without even scorching the cup.

91
00:06:45,978 --> 00:06:48,219
This is going to end in tears.

92
00:06:48,214 --> 00:06:49,738
OK.

93
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:04,045
Aagh!

94
00:07:05,837 --> 00:07:08,442
Er, haven't quite got
the calibration right yet.

95
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:15,671
Jack, there's been another attack.
Assault with a hypodermic.

96
00:07:15,668 --> 00:07:17,795
Only this time, the victim survived.

97
00:07:17,785 --> 00:07:20,310
Woman, aged 27.
She's in the hospital.

98
00:07:20,303 --> 00:07:23,181
Medical records wiped,
just like the others.

99
00:07:28,531 --> 00:07:31,295
Yeah, but the doctors
said they'd finished with me.

100
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:34,327
We're a bit different.
We know this is tough on you, Marie.

101
00:07:34,328 --> 00:07:37,013
But did you recognise
the man who attacked you?

102
00:07:37,005 --> 00:07:41,362
I already told the police.
We're different from them, too.
No, I never seen him before.

103
00:07:41,359 --> 00:07:44,647
Did he say anything
in the course of the attack? No.

104
00:07:44,636 --> 00:07:46,558
Open wide.

105
00:07:46,552 --> 00:07:50,636
Look, he just,
he came towards me with a great
big bloody needle, didn't he?

106
00:07:50,629 --> 00:07:54,952
You know, my dog bit him and then
I kicked him in the nuts. Respect!

107
00:07:57,464 --> 00:07:59,739
MUSIC: "Feel Good Inc" by Gorillaz

108
00:08:12,566 --> 00:08:14,056
This is a. . .three four.

109
00:08:25,631 --> 00:08:28,282
So you and Jack go back a long way?

110
00:08:28,271 --> 00:08:31,229
Forward and back, really.

111
00:08:31,228 --> 00:08:33,992
What brought you together?

112
00:08:33,986 --> 00:08:36,944
Let's say we were
under the same doctor.

113
00:08:39,096 --> 00:08:43,533
These killings -
why the ammonium hydroxide?
It's a weird way to kill someone.

114
00:08:43,530 --> 00:08:46,738
Yeah, it's gross. It's like
injecting them with bleach.

115
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:50,413
Unless the objective
isn't just killing.

116
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:53,771
It's destroying something
in the victim's bloodstream.

117
00:08:53,762 --> 00:08:56,560
It's getting rid of evidence!

118
00:08:56,558 --> 00:09:00,005
Locally, we've got a murder victim
and a survivor.

119
00:08:59,995 --> 00:09:03,761
Both attacked with hypodermics, both
with their medical records wiped.

120
00:09:03,753 --> 00:09:05,232
And more cases across the UK.

121
00:09:05,230 --> 00:09:08,757
We think the point of the attacks
is to destroy evidence
of their medical condition.

122
00:09:08,747 --> 00:09:12,183
Gwen, Ianto, pursue
the criminal investigation. OK.

123
00:09:12,181 --> 00:09:14,502
Martha, Owen will follow up
with the medical side. Fine.

124
00:09:14,498 --> 00:09:17,376
Tosh, any luck in retrieving
those medical records? Not yet.

125
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:20,094
I'm gonna have to dig down
into the system memories,

126
00:09:20,092 --> 00:09:23,095
see if I can find any remnants
of deleted or temporary files.

127
00:09:23,090 --> 00:09:25,217
Completely illegally, of course.

128
00:09:25,209 --> 00:09:28,770
Do what you have to.
We're not dealing with a freak
with some needle fetish.

129
00:09:28,766 --> 00:09:30,529
This is a conspiracy.

130
00:09:30,523 --> 00:09:33,924
Ianto, the police have found
another body in Heath Park.

131
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:37,127
It's got all the hallmarks
of the other attacks.

132
00:09:37,117 --> 00:09:39,756
I'll get Gwen, head out there now.

133
00:09:51,819 --> 00:09:53,423
What have you got?

134
00:09:53,416 --> 00:09:57,295
Body was found early this morning.
Caucasian male, early 20s.
OK, thanks.

135
00:10:01,448 --> 00:10:04,372
Who is he? Barry Leonard. Student.

136
00:10:04,367 --> 00:10:07,165
Doctor said it looked like. . .
Toxic shock.

137
00:10:11,638 --> 00:10:15,836
The attack took place in the woods,
so no witnesses, no CCTV.

138
00:10:15,835 --> 00:10:17,234
Same as the others.

139
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:21,317
Yeah. Tosh just checked Barry's
medical records - already wiped.

140
00:10:21,310 --> 00:10:24,837
The puncture mark on his eyeball was
identical to the other victims.

141
00:10:24,827 --> 00:10:26,135
I mean, Jack's right.

142
00:10:26,135 --> 00:10:30,105
These attacks are not random,
they're clinical. Professional.

143
00:10:30,098 --> 00:10:31,781
More like assassinations.

144
00:10:31,775 --> 00:10:35,495
Except Barry Leonard was a student.
Who'd assassinate a student?

145
00:10:35,491 --> 00:10:39,257
Student Loans Company. Yeah, yeah,
I think you've just cracked it.

146
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:41,810
But why delete medical records?

147
00:10:41,806 --> 00:10:46,891
You know, what did all these people
have in common? Owen's analysing
Marie's test results now.

148
00:10:46,883 --> 00:10:51,081
So we've got no idea where the
killer will strike next and the
attacks are getting more frequent.

149
00:10:51,076 --> 00:10:53,840
We keep looking, Gwen,
we'll find something.

150
00:10:53,835 --> 00:10:55,632
'Martha, call from the hospital.

151
00:10:55,631 --> 00:10:57,792
'Marie's had some sort of seizure.'

152
00:10:57,791 --> 00:11:00,191
They want us at the hospital.
Marie's collapsed.

153
00:11:00,188 --> 00:11:03,635
Yeah? My money's on this stuff. From
Marie's blood. It's a new one on me.

154
00:11:03,625 --> 00:11:07,300
Yeah, me too. Have you run
an isoenzyme analysis on it?

155
00:11:07,297 --> 00:11:10,539
No, not yet. What are you thinking?
Parasitic infection? Could be.

156
00:11:10,536 --> 00:11:14,529
It's got to be down to this stuff,
or I haven't got a clue
what's wrong with her.

157
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:17,454
Yeah - no infections,
no deficiencies in organ function,

158
00:11:17,448 --> 00:11:23,603
perfect cholesterol levels,
ideal blood pressure. Yeah, exactly.
She's so normal, she's abnormal.

159
00:11:23,601 --> 00:11:26,729
Marie? Marie, can you hear me?

160
00:11:26,719 --> 00:11:28,198
Mmm, yeah.

161
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:33,678
OK, you've got something
in your blood that
we don't recognise, all right?

162
00:11:33,672 --> 00:11:35,754
We think it's behind
your current illness

163
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:39,151
and we need to know what's been
happening to you so we can help you.

164
00:11:39,147 --> 00:11:41,388
Well, you're the doctors.
You tell me.

165
00:11:44,658 --> 00:11:49,220
'Barry was my best mate.
We were doing the same course.'

166
00:11:49,215 --> 00:11:50,864
Met him on the first day.

167
00:11:50,855 --> 00:11:53,858
Was Barry doing
any sort of drugs at all?

168
00:11:53,849 --> 00:11:56,329
Well, he used to be really clean.

169
00:11:56,326 --> 00:12:00,808
Reckoned he had to be careful
about what went into his body
because of his diabetes.

170
00:12:00,803 --> 00:12:02,043
Barry was diabetic?

171
00:12:02,043 --> 00:12:06,639
Sure. But when they cured that,
he was doing booze, blow. . .

172
00:12:06,636 --> 00:12:10,481
Wait a minute. You're telling me
Barry's diabetes was cured? Sure.

173
00:12:10,471 --> 00:12:14,430
That's impossible. Well, he stopped
taking insulin. He was fine.

174
00:12:14,428 --> 00:12:18,706
Owen, something you should know.
So who performed this miracle cure?

175
00:12:18,702 --> 00:12:20,340
He was very quiet about that.

176
00:12:20,339 --> 00:12:23,297
All I know is, he was suddenly
flashing a load of wedge about.

177
00:12:23,296 --> 00:12:27,335
Barry Leonard is said to
have recovered from diabetes.

178
00:12:27,334 --> 00:12:29,370
Thanks, Ianto.

179
00:12:29,370 --> 00:12:32,214
Listen, Marie,
you're gonna have to level with us.

180
00:12:32,208 --> 00:12:36,895
This could be a matter of
life and death. Have you ever
had a serious medical condition?

181
00:12:36,885 --> 00:12:38,682
Too good to be true.

182
00:12:38,681 --> 00:12:40,683
What do you mean?

183
00:12:40,679 --> 00:12:43,489
I had HIV.

184
00:12:43,479 --> 00:12:47,279
You're perfectly clear of antibodies.
That's not medically possible.

185
00:12:47,273 --> 00:12:51,198
That's the Reset. Reset?
What are we talking about? A drug?

186
00:12:51,194 --> 00:12:54,755
Right, I'm not familiar with Reset,
so any idea of a chemical name?

187
00:13:01,695 --> 00:13:04,539
Where d'you get it from, Marie?
I got it from the Pharm. The farm?

188
00:13:04,535 --> 00:13:08,130
What farm?
No, P-H-A-R-M, the Pharm.

189
00:13:08,128 --> 00:13:10,813
It's a medical research place,
all right?

190
00:13:10,806 --> 00:13:13,286
How did you get it from there?
They gave it to me.

191
00:13:13,286 --> 00:13:18,201
They paid me a lot of money. They
said I should to keep quiet about
it cos it was part of the contract.

192
00:13:18,199 --> 00:13:21,282
Are you saying you were
a clinical trial subject?

193
00:13:21,277 --> 00:13:23,643
Marie? Convulsing. Marie!

194
00:13:23,634 --> 00:13:26,432
I'll give her another 10ml.

195
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:28,513
You're all right.

196
00:13:33,141 --> 00:13:36,065
MONITOR FLATLINES

197
00:13:39,296 --> 00:13:41,184
She's dead.

198
00:13:45,810 --> 00:13:48,768
BUZZING

199
00:13:51,164 --> 00:13:54,201
Emergency! Get us out of here!

200
00:13:54,201 --> 00:13:58,126
BUZZING INCREASES

201
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:11,782
So it's an alien larva,
incubating in human bodies.

202
00:14:11,781 --> 00:14:13,499
We've never seen anything like it.

203
00:14:13,498 --> 00:14:15,819
So it left Marie's body
when she died,

204
00:14:15,818 --> 00:14:18,855
looking for another host
for its next stage of development.

205
00:14:18,855 --> 00:14:21,062
Which could have been us. Yeah.

206
00:14:21,052 --> 00:14:24,374
Fortunately, when they didn't
find one quickly, they died.

207
00:14:24,369 --> 00:14:27,054
I wonder what this cute
little larva grows up to be?

208
00:14:28,563 --> 00:14:32,249
This, folks, is a molecular model
of the drug that
we found in Marie's blood.

209
00:14:32,761 --> 00:14:34,717
She called it Reset.
So what does it do?

210
00:14:34,717 --> 00:14:38,323
Think about when you run a virus
scan through your computer, yeah?

211
00:14:38,313 --> 00:14:41,111
The software works its way through
the files and when it finds

212
00:14:41,112 --> 00:14:44,639
a Trojan or a virus or whatever,
identifies it and then deletes it.

213
00:14:44,628 --> 00:14:47,392
That is what this stuff does
to the human body.

214
00:14:47,382 --> 00:14:52,024
But it's not just viruses.
It's harmful bacteria, toxins,
even mutant cells, you name it.

215
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:55,057
It's like the body's been turned
back to its factory settings.

216
00:14:55,056 --> 00:14:56,853
It's the ultimate magic bullet.

217
00:14:56,853 --> 00:15:00,095
Supersedes anything and everything
in the pharmacological armoury.

218
00:15:00,091 --> 00:15:03,891
That would be the greatest medical
discovery in history. Exactly.

219
00:15:03,886 --> 00:15:07,322
Except, it comes bundled
with a lethal alien parasite.

220
00:15:07,322 --> 00:15:09,927
Ah, not so good a discovery.

221
00:15:09,922 --> 00:15:12,686
The parasite needs a healthy body
until it's incubated.

222
00:15:12,678 --> 00:15:15,920
So the parasite egg
incorporates this magic bullet,

223
00:15:15,916 --> 00:15:19,955
which puts everything in the system
back to its factory settings. Reset.

224
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:21,474
Neato.

225
00:15:21,470 --> 00:15:26,146
So who runs the Pharm? Well,
the public image is innocent enough.

226
00:15:26,141 --> 00:15:30,749
Private-public partnership between
the government and a consortium
of the pharmaceutical companies.

227
00:15:30,738 --> 00:15:33,775
Researching and developing
cutting-edge biotechnology.

228
